inn1.comm: off the mark, good line, just a fraction outside off, pushed wide of extra cover to pinch a quick single
short of a good length on the of, pushes at it off the back foot, gets a thick edge down to third man for a single
charges ahead, just a hint, and then opts to leave it go as it lands in the channel outside off
good length on the off,. driven crisply but straight to extra cover, well connected
beaten, bowled at 135.9 kmph, darted away from a short of a good length on the off stump to just escape the outside edge as he tried to keep it down
beaten again, much fuller this time, angling away from him, leaves him as he prods at it
misfield! Pushed off the front foot to extra cover and a fumble allows them a single
driven on the up and firmly, pitched up outside off, he leans into it and cracks it wide of mid-off for the first boundary of the day
angling in towards middle, presents the straight bat while driving it towards mid-on
he's striking them well, fullish on the off, timed beautifully but straight to mid-off
short of a good length on middle, maintains its line, not much movement for Gul here, pushed back to the bowler
shortish on the off, slower one there, bowled at 116.9 kmph, punches it past the bowler to mid-off
fullish outside off, bowled at 135.7 kmph, leaves it be, not tempted into the drive
short of a good length outside off this time, just leaving him a hint, lets it go
shortish outside off, getting it to leave the right hander, he watches it through, opting to stay patient early on
probing line, just a fraction outside off, defends it rock solid towards point
shortish outside off, plenty of width, slashes hard with a bent knee, flies off the outside edge over the slips wide of third man
similar attempt, gets it much squarer this time,uppish but well wide of point, down towards third man for a single
angling it on the pads, works it wide of mid-on for a couple of runs
lands on a good length on the off, defended wide of extra cover, thinks of a single but he's sent back in time
bangs it hard on middle, tries to work it square from the crease, rapped on the thighs, sneaks a run as it rolls over into the off side
pushed it full on the off, defended watchfully to mid-off, bowled at 135 kmph
short of a good length on the off, taps it back to the bowler who needlessly hurls it back onto the stumps at the striker's end, conceding a run off the ricochet in the process
short on the off, chops it down towards point
short on the off and shoots off the pitch, tries to play the upper-cut, doesn't connect
short of a length on the off, cuts it down towards point
shortish on the off, gets back and taps it down onto the pitch
easily done, knocks it down just wide of extra cover and steals a run
out comes the pull but doesn't connect it all too well, deliberately played it down towards fine leg for a single
beaten for the third time in the innings by Aamer, testing length outside off and moves away after landing, beating his attempted push
short on the off, pushes it uppishly towards cover
appeal for lbw, short of a good length outside off, darts in, first time for Gul, gets across the line to work it past midwicket, gets an inside edge onto his pads, that can't be given
shortish on the off, punched off the back foot to cover
goes for the pull but it comes onto him a little too quickly, short on middle, tries to smack it past square, is struck on the chest
full on the off, drives it with a bit of a flourish past the outstretched hands of Gul down to mid-off where a diving stop saves a few runs
shortish on the off, guides it down to third man for a single
play and a miss, short and wide, slashes at it, doesn't make contact
short of a good length on the off, eases it past a diving point for a single to third man
fooled by the slightly slower one, the offcutter at 125 kmph, swung hard at it but it cut away to roll down to the keeper
connects this time, came onto him at the right pace, short on the off and he got into position early, rocking forward and smashing it over square leg
shuffled a long way across, pitched outside leg and tried to glance it fine, missed the bat but brushed the pads to beat the diving keeper to the fine-leg boundary
short on the off, gets back and knocks it down towards point
a fraction short outside off, cuts it down all along the ground to third man for a single
ominous signs these, slower one but right in the slot outside off, he picked it and thumped it over mid-off for a flat six
giving him the charge and adjusting well to the length, shortish and he chops it wide of point for a quick single
bouncer, no problems dealing with that one, called a wide, he ducked under it comfortably
held it back again, bowls it short on the off, mistimes a cut down to point
crunched but straight to the fielder, short and wide again, he slaps it hard but can't beat cover point
almost jinxed him there, short on the off, a touch too quick for him as he gets it really high on the bat as he goes for the pull, airy but lands safe wide of mid-on
he's dominating this stand alright, that was absolutely punished, bowled it short on middle, in the zone for McCullum who pulls it hard and flat over square leg for his second maximum
back of a length again but not as much as the previous one, pushed back to the bowler
held it back outside off, taps it down towards cover off the back foot
the pull is out again but all along the ground this time and down towards a protective deep midwicket

between slip and keeper, a widish slip was in place and he bisected the gap perfectly though not intentionally, rose up to him after landing short on the off, went for the cut, got a thick edge and earned a streaky four
bowled on a good length on the off, defended back towards the bowler
smashed, his third six, another short one, he favours that zone and duly deposits it over square leg for another big one, poor length, little learnt from prior experience
short of a length again, and a misfield, lets it through his legs at point and allows them a couple more

brilliantly fielded but run out missed, full toss outside off, driven wide of mid-off where Younis Khan hurls himself to his left and returns a strong throw at the keeper's end with McCullum well short, Kamran hasn't run in to collect it, Younis misses, giving McCullum just the time he needs to make it back
short outside of, chopped wide of point, gets a run
pitched up a fraction and he's onto it, gets forward and slaps it with utter disdain past extra cover and mid-off for a boundary
pushed off the back foot wide of midwicket for a single
short of a good length on the off, a hint of inward movement, played back to the bowler
strayed on the pads there, flicked away into the deep on the leg side for a single
bowled it from wide of the crease, angled it into middle and leg, pushed firmly past midwicket for two more, easily done
short and wide, there's point in the deep and McCullum slashes it down towards him for a single
hurls it on a good length on the off, stands tall and punches it to extra cover
hurled it on a good length on the off, opened the face there and pushed it wide of point for a single
bouncer, well bowled this time at 134.3, on middle and McCullum gets down in time
bouncer again, much more effort involved in this time, banged in hard on middle and it's too high, given a wide

gone! Redmond is Gul's 100th ODI wicket, short of a length on the off, comes down the track and tries to slap it past the bowler, gets a top edge and it lands safely into the palms of Aamer at third man
good length on the off, gets front and across and defends it back to the bowler
nicely timed, short of a length outside off, gets forward, opens the face and just directs it past a diving point to beat third man to the ropes
on middle and leg, shuffles a hint and defends it to midwicket
tossed up on the off, turns in a hint, defended to extra cover
a high backlift there, brings it down and crunches it to extra cover
flat, bowled on a good length on middle, driven down to long-on for a single
short on middle, gets back and punches it down to long-on for one more
threw it up slightly this time, pushed through to midwicket
floats it at 89.8 kmph, on middle and leg, played through the line to long-on for a single
short of a good length on the off, pushed off the back foot to point
back of a length on the off, gets behind it nicely and defends it down to Gul
short of a good length on middle, pushed away off the back foot down towards deep midwicket for a single
hurls it short on middle, pushes him back and he drops it in front of the bowler
the inswinging yorker, in the blockhole on the off, dug out well by Guptill
trying it again, bowls it full on the off, driven through the line to mid-off
threw it up outside off, slightly short, turns back in, thinks of a cut but then restrains himself
flat, bowled on a good length on middle, pushed to midwicket
pushed through towards long-on for a single
presents a straight bat while driving it wide of Ajmal, who dives to his right to save a single
keeping them quiet, flat, bowled on a good length on the off, played straight to cover
well done, just a single, punched towards long-on, Ajmal's done well to haul things back just a little
lands on a good length on the off, driven straight to mid-off
misfield by Afridi, bowled on middle and leg, drove it wide of midwicket where Afridi made a mess of an attempted slide, conceding a single
reaches his half-century, punches it between cover and point for a single, a timely return to form in the previous game and he's continuing it

appeal for a catch, short on the off, stopped on him a touch, pushed it uppishly back to the bowler who dives forward but takes it on the half-volley, holds it up in a stifled appeal but the replays clearly show that fell short.
short on on the off, taps it back onto the pitch
punched hard off the back foot between extra cover and mid-off, but he is unable to pierce the in-field, just a single
pushed through midwicket down into the deep for a single
shortish on middle, punched down to long-on for one more

the doosra does the trick, played for the spin there, trying to work it through the leg side, got a leading edge as it went the other way and Younis Khan at mid-off did well running to his left and taking a testing chance
pushed off the front foot to midwicket
pushed through quick, full and fast on middle dug out back to the  bowler
lands on a good length on the off, defended off the front foot wide of midwicket for a quick single
fullish on the off, driven back to the bowler who palms it to extra cover
McCullum is unrelenting, continues to punish those short ones, doesn't rock back, stays his ground and swings it past midwicket for a boundary
pushed through slightly fuller and he attempts a similar shot but the length just isn't right, mistimes it to square leg
short and wide, Taylor is away, a thick outside edge to third man as he slashes hard
four more, short again and he creams it through the off side, swatting the poor thing mercilessly between cover and point
the one that went straight on, took the leading edge but he played it gently, wide of point for a single
tosses it up on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
driven through the line wide of the bowler down to long-on
short on leg stump, whips it away fine for a couple of runs
pushed off the front foot wide of midwicket for a single
played it well there, picked the straighter one, opened the face just slightly, guiding it wide of point
starts off with one down the leg side, fired it down and Taylor failed to connect on an attempt work towards fine leg
slaps it down towards deep square leg on a bent knee
pushed it off the front foot towards midwicket
tossed up on the off, driven uppishly down towards long-off for a single
short and wide, chops it down towards deep point for a single
short on middle, swivels and drags it down to fine leg for a single
short on middle, punched to long-on to rotate the strike
threw it up on middle, defended cautiously towards extra cover
worked away towards deep square leg for a single
bowled it short on leg stump, tucked away behind square for one more
hurls it short on the, off, darts in, rocks back and slaps it between long-off and deep cover for a couple of runs
tossed up on middle, driven back to the bowler
drilled through the off side towards deep cover for a single
kept it a little flat this time, defended with a lunge with bat close to pad
picked it beautifully, bowled it full, he had shaped up for a sweep and bisected the gap between deep square leg and deep midwicket
reaches forward and pushes it uppishly towards extra cover
slower through the air, made to reach again, defends it awkwardly into the off side
bowled on a good length on the off, pushed to extra cover
short of a length outside off, waits for it to turn in and taps it to short third
quicker through the air, cracks it back to the bowler all along the ground
that didn't turn, Taylor was expecting it to, tried to dab it behind the keeper, missed
Taylor opens up, was bogged down with those four consecutive dots and pulled off the slog-sweep, clearing deep midwicket with ease
follows it up with a single down towards long-on to keep the strike
bowled full on the off, driven through the line to long-off
flat, bowled on a good length on the off, defended to extra cover
threw it up on the off, driven down to long-off
short, and down the leg side, called a wide
the googly there, turned in and he didn't pick it, got an inside edge onto the pads as he leaned forward
tried to crack it hard but mistimed it to extra cover
the quicker one this time, pushed it back uppishly but well short of a diving Afridi
short of a good length on the off, defended back to the bowler
bowled it full on the off, driven down to long-off for a single
stands tall and punches it down to long-on for a single
bowls it full on middle and leg, played down to long-on again
three in a row, a middle and leg line this time, the fielder in the deep gets into the act again
slightly short on the off, plays it back down on the pitch
hurls it quick on middle and off, defends it watchfully back to Afridi
short of a length, turns away, leaves it be
pushes it through the line to long-off for a single
short of a length on the off, chopped down towards deep point for a single
bowled it full on middle, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
almost dragged it on, short on the off, goes for the cut but it turns in just a hint, chops it over the stumps, sneaks a single and brings up the 50-stand
pushed off the front foot back to the bowler

tame dismissal, turns in just a hint from a good length on the off, tries to close the face while playing the attempted drive to long-on, ends up scooping it straight back to Malik who makes no mistake
threw it up on middle, pushes it just wide of midwicket for a single
tossed up outside off, drops it in front of point and cover for a quick single
bowled flat outside off, eased down to deep cover for a single
loops it just outside off, he defends it with a still head in front of the bowler
bowled full on the off, driven hard but straight back at the stumps at the non-striker's end
pushed into the leg side off the front foot
hurls it full on middle, quicker one this time, driven down to wide long-on for a single
plays the paddle, had made up his mind, plays it down to fine leg for a single
threw it up outside off, driven down to long-on for a single
hurls it fast on middle,. plays it down to long-on again
fires it down the leg side, seen a few of those today, given a wide
tossed up outside off, turns in, defended into the off side
flighted on middle, closes the face, plays it into the leg side for a single
threw it up on leg stump, swept it straight down to short fine leg
short of a good length on the off, knocks it past the bowler for one more
bowled at 90.2 kmph, guides it between point and cover for a single
short of a good length on middle, works it down to midwicket
falls safe, tossed up outside off and was spinning away, attempted the slog-sweep, miscued it wide of long-on, wide of the converging substitute fielder
bowled it on a good length on middle, worked it wide of midwicket for a single
on middle and leg, scoops it down to fine leg for a single
short and wide, holds its line, thinks of a cut but then opts out
hurled it quick and flat outside off, square-driven towards deep point for a single
short on middle, pushed to midwicket from the crease
shuffled across, he bowled it quick, whipped it between deep square leg and deep midwicket for a couple of runs
pushed off the front foot back to the bowler
short on the off, stays his ground and jabs it to midwicket
lands on a good length outside off, cracks it straight back to Afridi
threw it up outside off, went for the slog-sweep, got a top edge but it landed well safe of short third man
too quick, short, outside off, bowled at 93 kmph, went for the cut but it zipped past him
short of a good length on the off, pushed towards extra cover
the googly there, closes the face and works it wide of midwicket for a single
threw it up outside off, guided it wide of point for a single
short on the off, rocks back and punches it down to long-on for a single
flat on middle and leg, tickles it behind square for one more
hurled it short, slaps it from the crease back to the bowler
bowled it full on middle, flicked away towards deep square leg for a single
run-out attempt, closes the face to turn it towards midwicket, steals a quick single but Umar Akmal missed an attempt at a direct-hit at the non-striker's end
short and wide, cuts it down to point from the crease
bowls it full on the off, driven back to the bowler

run out, goes for the cut, gets an inside edge towards short fine, Taylor calls for the single, Styris responds but is caught off-guard as Butt targets the non-striker's end and scores a direct hit to find Styris just short of his ground
tossed up on middle, defended with a lunge to the bowler
bowled full on middle, driven down to long-on for a single
worked away into the leg side wide of midwicket for a single
quicker one, bowled at 99.1 kmph, goes for the cut but is surprised by the pace
bowled it full on middle and leg, driven wide of long-on for a couple of runs
threw it up on middle, paddled down to fine leg for a single
short on the off, taps it in front of midwicket for one more
bowls it full on middle, drags it down in typical style to fine leg for a single
drops a dolly, short of a good length, tries to work it into the leg side, gets a leading edge and Aamer spills the easiest of catches
the shot works this time, gets it through midwicket for one more
short of a good length on the off, crunched straight to cover
lands on a good length, drops it just wide of the bowler for a single
bowled full on the off, worked away to deep square leg
banged in short on the off, drops it short of point with soft hands to steal the single
on middle and leg, worked away behind square for a single
threw it up on the off, swept wide of deep square leg for a couple more
lands on a good length on the off, pushed down to long-on for one more
short of a good length on the off, punched down to long-on
the sweep again, down towards deep backward square leg
the doosra, he picked it, had time as it spun away from a short of a length, punched past the bowler for another single
lands on a good length on the off, pushed down towards long-off for a single
nicely played, walks across, closes the face and glides it to deep square leg
shortish on the off, knocks it wide of the bowler in the off side for a single
a good bouncer, short on the off, ducks under it at the right time
well played, bowled it short outside off, swiveled and helped it down to fine leg for a single
defends it with soft hands towards extra cover from the crease
short of a length on middle, works it in the midwicket region for a single
on middle and off, gets front and across and drives it back to the bowler
trapped in front! Spun in sharply from a good length on the off stump, got forward and tried to turn it away towards midwicket, missed and was caught in line. Would have clipped leg stump
beaten by the doosra, full and wide, tried to open the face there, expecting it to turn into him, it goes the other way to beat the outside edge
short of a length on the off, defended off the back foot to the bowler
short of a length outside off, cuts it down towards deep point for a single
bowls it full on the off, driven through to extra cover from the crease

Caught in front! The googly does him in, shortish on the off and turned in sharply as he got all the way onto the back foot to whip it into the leg side, didn't pick it early and was caught high on the pads, would have gone on to hit middle and leg
gets front and across and defends it back to the bowler
quick full toss on leg stump, turned away to deep square leg for a single
threw it up on the off, driven down to long-off for a single

the middle order is crumbling now, deceived by the quicker one. Round the wicket, hurls it flat and quick, opts to play from the crease into the leg side as it turns in, he misses and is caught right in front of middle
beaten! The doosra to which he has no answer, leans forward to defend and it spins away
bowled full on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
similar, just a little wider, plays it in the direction of extra cover
the googly results in a stifled appeal for lbw, turns in and strikes him high on the pads
comes down the track, negates the turn and drives it down to long-on
the googly again, pitches outside leg and raps him on the pads as he goes for the sweep
tossed up outside off, goes for the reverse-paddle, misses
attempts an identical shot this time, gets a top edge down towards short third

Ajmal gets four! Short of a length on the off and drifts in towards middle, Oram is all the way back and misreads the line as he tries to work it into the leg side, is struck on the pads and the umpire had no hesitation
that was quick, bowled at 107 kmph, dug out towards cover
turned in from a good length on the off, went on straight and produced the leading edge which landed safe wide of point
goes for the paddle, takes it on the full, ends up playing it back to the bowler as it gets the bottom of the bat
guided off the back foot wide of point
short of a good length on the off, taps it in front of cover
leaves the right hander there, fishing for it from the crease, makes no contact
fullish on middle, pushed away wide of mid-on for a couple of runs, Ajmal gives chase
What a collapse! Short on the off, tried to slap it over mid-on, got it high on the bat and Ajmal ran a few paces to his left to pouch a straightforward chance
tossed up on the off, gets forward and defends it into the leg side
flighted it on the off, pushed it with a lunge towards extra cover
turns in from a good length outside off, defended back to the bowler
the doosra again, produces the leading edge, clears extra cover and he manages to steal a single to take the score to 200
defended into the off side off the front foot
full toss on middle, played down towards long-on for a single to end a successful spell
short on the off, guided behind point from the crease for a single
full and wide, driven straight to extra cover, Afridi aims at the non-striker's end, there's no one to back up and they get overthrows
hurled it short outside off, backs away from it
bowled it full on the off, driven down towards mid-off for a quick single
hurled it full outside off, pushed down wide of deep cover for a couple more to the score
manages to squeeze three runs, full and wide, steered behind point, Maliks runs across from deep point to kick that in just inside the ropes
short outside off, backs away from it as it leaves him
shortish on middle, dabbed in front of extra cover for a single
gone! Fullish, made room, picked it up but scooped it straight to midwicket to end the innings

inn2.comm: swinging in a touch, on middle and moving down leg, tries to work it away behind square, brushes the pads and they sneak a leg bye
lands on a good length on the off stump, defended towards cover from the crease
moving away a hint, withdraws his bat at the right time, gets it to land on a good length and leave the right hander
short of a good length on the off, tapped to extra cover from the crease
probing him outside off, bowled it at 127.5 kmph, cut away just a hint, defended it well with an open face to point

dropped, an early chance missed, a tough one, was testing him outside off, bowled it on a length, moved away and produced the outside edge but McCullum, who dived full length to his right, was unable to hang on
short of a good length on the off, knocked down towards cover from the crease
bowled at 119.3 kmph, trying to deceive him a little with the grunt, a touch too wide, left alone to the keeper
short of a length, chases it but it leaves him further, misses
lands on a good length outside off and angles away from the left-hander, left alone to the keeper
pitched it up outside off and Butt is in no aggressive mood, he has ample time and he's playing it out, shoulders arms
pushed off the back foot towards extra cover
nicely timed, short of a length, rocks back and punches it through point and cover, sweet sound of bat striking ball and they get three
short of a good length on leg stump, walks across to clip it behind square, is struck on the pads again, another leg bye
nicely done, short on middle, he pulls it away through square leg with ease to earn a boundary
beautifully timed, just a flick of the wrists, shortish on middle and leg, stays in his crease and jabs it through square leg for four more
three in a row, not much effort in any of those shots, just pure timing, short of a good length on the off, he punches it on the rise through mid-off and extra cover for another boundary
Butt cashes in, short, too much width, and he cuts it fiercely through point for the fourth consecutive boundary of the innings
flicked away to square leg, there's a slight fumble and they sneak a couple more
short of a good length on middle, turned away from the crease between mid-on and midwicket for another couple
well fielded by Broom at point, pushed it away from his body but pretty firmly, Broom dives well to his left to save a few more runs
banged in short outside off, leaves it be this time
short and wide, not much intent in that shot, just hangs his bat out and gets a top edge, he is fortunate that lands between point running back and third man converging
lands on a good length outside off, gets forward and shoulders arms to that one
full and wide, leans into the drove and strokes it well but it's fielded well at extra cover
pitched it up just a fraction outside off, defended solidly to extra cover
the bouncer on middle, bowled at 127.3 kmph, ducks under it
whipped away, short of a length on middle, moves across and works it firmly through midwicket for a boundary
bowled on a good length on the off, gets across and taps it back to the bowler
back of a length on the off, at 123.5 kmph, knocked back to the bowler
that will help, fired down the leg side, misses out on the glance, McCullum dives well to snap it this time
pitched up outside off, pushed between mid-off and extra cover for a single
bowled it short outside off, chops it wide of a diving Broom at point
short of a good length on the off, punched straight to extra cover
hurls it short on the off, taps it towards extra cover off the back foot
lands on a good length outside off, cracks it straight to short point, in full control of that shot
plenty of effort there, bowled at 136 kmph, short on middle, defended back to the bowler
straying on the pads,. gets forward and drives it sweetly but straight to midwicket
lands on a good length on middle at 124.7 kmph, pushed wide of mid-on for a quick single
hurls it in the blockhole outside off, dug out comfortably back to the bowler
crisply played, bowls it full on middle and Butt drives it back with a full face between mid-on and mid-off for three more
Latif's looked fluent after that shaky start, slightly short outside off, stands tall and square-drives it through point for two more
banged in short on middle, goes for the pull, doesn't come on to him as quick as he expected, struck on the arm
lands on a good length on the off, defended from the crease back to the bowler
banged in short outside off, a touch too wide and he doesn't bother chasing it
full and wide, there to hit and he chases it but doesn't connect
short and wide, terrible delivery, in his favoured zone, Butt takes full toll, smashing it between cover and point
hurls it full on the off, leans into the drive as he plays it to extra cover
there is a slip in place but that's way out of his reach, bowled full on the off, sucking him into the drive but Butt's fortunate, as he gets a thick outside edge to the third-man boundary
short of a good length outside off, holds its line, left alone

it looked out, Vettori's struck immediately! Drifted in, landed on a good length on the off and angled in, he didn't get too forward while trying to play at it, missed and was caught right in front of middle
tossed up on the off, reaches forward and defends it towards extra cover
bowled it full on the off, pushed it with a lunge back to the bowler
turned away after landing on a good length outside off, pushed towards cover
drifting in towards middle, worked away towards deep square leg to get off the mark
bowled on a good length on the off, defended towards cover
banged in short on middle, ducks under it well, working up some good pace now
back of a length on middle, rocks back and punches it to the bowler
nips back in from a good length on middle, Younis is a little surprised by the bounce, is struck high on the pads
superbly fielded by Southee at third man, bowled full and wide, steers it wide of slip, he runs across and slides to his left to drag it back in, brings up the 50
short of a good length on the off, punched off the back foot to the bowler
slower through the air, shortish on leg stump, worked away behind square for a single
angling in towards middle, bowled full, reaches forward and drops it on the pitch
threw it up outside off, lunges and drives it to extra cover
quick, he arm ball on middle, manages to get his bat to it just at the right time, chopping it down towards point
spins away to beat the attempted cut, good turn there and was slow through the air, he didn't pick it

run out again, Butt has to go. Pushed off the front foot towards extra cover, Younis takes off but there's plenty of hesitation from Butt who is late in his response, Guptill flicks an under-arm throw to the keeper who takes off the bails to find him miles short

Younis goes! New Zealand have fought back, short of a good length on the off, just a hint of away movement, Younis moves back to defend, gets a thick outside edge and Taylor at a widish slip takes a good low catch diving to his left
banged in short outside off at 133.2 kmph, moves away and he lets it go
angling it in towards middle and leg, tries to work it fine, clips his pads and they get a couple of leg byes
